Vice President Kamala Harris met with Barbadian Prime Minister Mia Amor Mottley to discuss the U.S.-Barbados bilateral relationship and the U.S.' commitment to the Caribbean. They focused on creating economic opportunities in the region and accelerating COVID-19 recovery. Vice President Harris thanked Prime Minister Mottley for her leadership on climate crisis issues and discussed incorporating climate adaptation into economic recovery plans. The Vice President reaffirmed the U.S.' commitment to working with countries like Barbados that suffer the impacts of climate change. They also discussed supporting Haiti and the Haitian people through collaboration between the United States and CARICOM.